Title: Mubarak Steps Down
Description: Demonstrators on Tahrir Square, Cairo, react to a televised speech on 10 February, in which contrary to prior expectations, Egypt’s president Hosni Mubarak said he would not give up power.

Title: Never Let You Go
Description: Marcos and Monica were married for 65 years and, for much of that time, lived in the same apartment in Buenos Aires. In 2007, aged 84, Monica was diagnosed with Alzheimer’s. Since that moment, Marcos devoted his time to taking care of her.

Title: Bolivianas
Description: Bolivia is home to some 36 indigenous groups. The country’s president, Evo Morales, the first indigenous Bolivian to hold that office, is leader of the Movement towards Socialism party, whose long-held goal has been the integration of indigenous communities into national life.

Title: Bolivianas

Title: Bolivianas
Description: A worker rests on a mound of coca leaves in central Bolivia, the president’s power base. President Morales stresses that the plant is intrinsic to local culture, not just the raw material for cocaine.

Description: A woman in traditional dress presents a national television news program.

Title: Earthquake in Japan

Title: Cliff-Climbing Polar Bear Attempting to Eat Seabird Eggs

Title: Battle for Libya
Description: After security forces fired live rounds on demonstrators in Libya’s second city of Benghazi, in mid-February, anti-government protests escalated. Over the next few months, opposition to the rule of long-time dictator Colonel Muammar Gaddafi became a full-scale national revolt.

Title: Battle for Libya
Description: An opposition fighter gives a victory sign, while fighting on the front line at Ras Lanuf, on 11 March.

Title: Battle for Libya
Description: A funeral takes place in a cemetery in Benghazi.

Title: Battle for Libya
Description: Opposition fighters launch an attack on loyalist forces hiding out in Ajdabiya, 150 kilometers south of Benghazi, on 25 April.

Title: Battle for Libya
Description: Opposition fighters sing and celebrate, during the battle for the key oil town of Ras Lanuf, on 11 March.

Title: Battle for Libya
Description: A building on the outskirts of Ajdabiya shows scars of shelling by Gaddafi military. Ajdabiya was a strategic stop on the road to the ‘rebel capital’ Benghazi in the east.

Title: Battle for Libya
Description: Libyans in Misrata, which had been besieged for months by Gaddafi forces, celebrate the liberation of the country, on 24 October.

Title: Battle for Libya
Description: A young Libyan shows off the gun he has taken from the Gaddafi family compound, in Tripoli, on 23 September.

Title: Battle for Libya
Description: Rebel fighters conduct an assault on the Gaddafi family compound, Tripoli, on 23 September.

Title: Battle for Libya
Description: Rebels capture an alleged mercenary in Tripoli, on 25 September. Gaddafi was accused of hiring armed support from other African countries.

Title: Tsunami Aftermath
Description: Tsunami waves created by a massive earthquake off the northeastern shores of Japan caused wide-ranging destruction along the coast. Overwhelming the three worst-hit prefectures with an estimated 22.63 million tons of debris.

Title: Tsunami Aftermath
Description: Tsunami waves created by a massive earthquake off the northeastern shores of Japan caused wide-ranging destruction along the coast. Iwate, Miyagi, and Fukushima—the three worst-hit prefectures—were overwhelmed by an estimated 22.63 million tons of debris.

Title: Japan's Nuclear Refugees
Description: The Tohoku earthquake and subsequent tsunami in Japan damaged vital cooling systems at the Fukushima Daiichi nuclear power plant. A 20-kilometer exclusion zone was declared around the plant, and more than 80,000 people were evacuated.

Title: Japan's Nuclear Refugees
Description: Dogs fight on the deserted streets of Okuma, near the Fukushima Daiichi nuclear power plant, on 5 June.

Title: Japan's Nuclear Refugees
Description: An unmade bed, in Okuma, less than five kilometers from the damaged Fukushima Daiichi nuclear power plant, is testament to a hasty exodus. Evacuation orders were broadcast during a televised news conference before dawn on 12 March.

Title: Japan's Nuclear Refugees
Description: Grass sprouts from a wrecked car, more than four months after the Fukushima nuclear incident.

Title: Japan's Nuclear Refugees
Description: Coveted leather book bags remain in the cubby holes of a hastily evacuated classroom, months after the Fukushima nuclear incident. Children receive regular evacuation drills, so knew what to do, but were expecting to return in a few days.

Title: Japan's Nuclear Refugees
Description: An animal rights activist walks within half a kilometer of Fukushima Daiichi. Animal rescuers defied restrictions to aid abandoned pets and livestock.

Title: Japan's Nuclear Refugees
Description: The carcass of a cow lies in a farmyard within the contaminated nuclear exclusion zone, in July. No provision was made to evacuate pets or livestock following the Fukushima nuclear incident.

Title: Japan's Nuclear Refugees
Description: Fukushima Daiichi nuclear power plant on 8 November, nearly eight months after the tsunami.

Title: Japan's Nuclear Refugees
Description: In a gym in Hirono, on 8 June, former residents of the exclusion zone are briefed before an escorted visit to their homes to retrieve a few small items.

Title: Japan's Nuclear Refugees
Description: Nobuko Sanpei (74) eats dinner in her cardboard-box home, in an evacuee shelter at a convention center, in June. She cut a window into the wall because it was too hot inside.

Title: Radio Haiti
Description: More than 50 percent of Haitians are illiterate, and only 25 percent have regular access to electricity, which means that battery-operated radios are the country’s main medium.

Title: Tsunami
Description: A woman cries amidst the ruins of the town of Natori, on 13 March, two days after the tsunami that devastated much of Japan’s northeastern coast.

Title: Hanging in Iran

Description: A convicted rapist is taken for execution. He was one of a group of more than a dozen men, who invaded a private party in Khomeinishahr, tied up male guests or locked them in rooms, and raped a number of the women.

Title: Infinite Cave

Title: Infinite Cave
Description: Down in the big chamber of Long Con, a new discovery in 2010 and continuation of the Alcove of Hang Son Doong. Between 10.30 and 15.00 sunlight can reach the ground and produce a miniature weather system in the chamber: increased humidity creates condensation inside the cool cave atmosphere and leads to the formation of clouds.

Description: Giant Stalagmite and Big passage with Gareth ‘Sweeney’ Sewell in the background on the Hand of Dog.

Title: Rhino Wars
Description: With rhinoceros horn worth more than gold, the animals are the target of poachers. South Africa alone lost over 400 rhinos to illegal poaching in 2011. It is estimated there are only 16,000 rhinos left in the world, and the animal faces extinction.

Title: Rhino Wars
Description: A black rhino, which had already been de-horned by a vet to protect it, wanders in the bush after poachers shot it four times, tore out the stump of the horn, and left it for dead. The wound became infected and though treated with antibiotics, the animal later died.

Title: Rhino Wars
Description: After some supervision by rangers at Tugela Private Game Reserve, in South Africa, a male rhino has taken a female whose horn had been removed by poachers, using a chain saw, under its protection.

Title: Rhino Wars
Description: The carcass of a white rhino, which was snared and killed for its horns, lies in the Selati private game reserve.

Title: Rhino Wars
Description: A white rhino and her calf walk in the bush at the Hluhluwe-Umfolozi Game Reserve. The reserve is the world’s largest repository of rhino, providing shelter to some 2,300 in total.

Title: Rhino Wars
Description: A white rhino skin is salted for curing after a morning hunt, on Dawie Groenewald’s game farm, near the town of Musina. The South African government allows some rhino hunting under permit.

Title: Rhino Wars
Description: Dawie Groenewald, his wife, and 11 vet and hunter employees, attend their trial in Musina, South Africa, accused of transgressing the Endangered Species Act, after unaccounted-for rhino carcasses were found on his game farm.

Title: Rhino Wars
Description: A member of the International Anti-Poaching Foundation leads a training workshop for rhino-protection rangers.

Title: Rhino Wars
Description: A vet on a game farm de-horns a white rhino, as a precautionary anti-poaching measure.

Title: Rhino Wars
Description: A black rhino is in transit after being captured as part of a security translocation program, transferring the animal to a safer location, at the Hluhluwe-Imfolozi Game Reserve.

Title: Strelka
Description: In the amateur street fighting tournament known as strelka in Russia, fighters compete on sand without a time limit. Only a knockout or surrender stops the fight.

Title: Burke + Norfolk
Description: While working in Afghanistan during 2011, Simon Norfolk had the idea of trying to photograph groups he felt might have been interesting to the 19th-century photographer John Burke, were he there today.

Title: Shark Fin
Description: Hunting sharks for their fins has become big business across the globe, as shark-fin soup soars in popularity among China’s growing, newly affluent middle class. Up to 73 million sharks are killed annually.

Title: Evicted
Description: Americans experienced the fifth year of a national housing crisis. By the end of 2011, some four million families had lost their homes after they could no longer meet mortgage payments. People renting houses often found themselves in a similar situation, no longer able to afford the rent and facing eviction.

Title: Evicted
Description: An eviction team moves a mattress onto the street in Longmont, Colorado.

Title: Evicted
Description: One-year-old Chase Milam watches as a sheriff’s deputy and a member of an eviction team remove possessions from his aunt’s home in Milliken, Colorado. His aunt, Brandie Barbiere, whose child-care business had dropped by more than half, had stopped making mortgage payments 11 months earlier.

Title: Evicted
Description: The contents of a child’s room lie outside the Barbiere’s house in Milliken, after the family had been evicted.

Title: Evicted
Description: Brandie and Dan Barbiere sit among their possessions after eviction from their home, in Milliken. Brandie, whose child-care business had dropped by more than half due to the weak economy, had stopped making mortgage payments 11 months earlier.

Title: Evicted
Description: Julie Holzhauer folds her daughter’s sweater, in front of her former home, after the family has been evicted for not paying the rent.

Title: Evicted
Description: Olivia Holzhauer (9) hugs her dog after her family had been evicted from their home, after falling into arrears with the rent.

Title: Evicted
Description: Julie and John Holzhauer’s wedding photo lies among possessions spread over the front lawn during the eviction. John, a building contractor, had lost 40 percent of his business due to the economic recession.

Title: Evicted
Description: Children lie in an empty living-room, after an eviction team had removed the household furniture.

Title: Evicted
Description: Julie Holzhauer stands among family possessions, on the front lawn of her former home, following eviction after falling behind with the rent.

Title: Tsunami
Description: On 11 March, a magnitude 9.0 earthquake struck 70 kilometers off the Tohoku coast, in northeastern Japan. The quake triggered a tsunami that swept inland, destroying buildings, crippling infrastructure, and resulting in the displacement of more than 340,000 people.

Title: Tsunami
Description: Fisherman Yutaka Watanabe sits on the roof of a destroyed house, while looking for missing family members.

Title: Tsunami
Description: Chieko Matsukawa holds up her daughter’s graduation certificate, which she salvaged from the ruins of their home in Higashimatsushima.

Title: Tsunami
Description: A wrecked train balances over a cemetery in Onagawa.

Title: Tsunami
Description: Hira Noda (70) collects salvageable items, in her village, which has been devastated by the tsunami.

Title: Tsunami
Description: A man looks for family photos in boxes of personal belongings recovered from the debris left by the tsunami, in a gymnasium, on 18 April.

Title: Tsunami
Description: Illuminated by car headlights, tsunami survivor Tadao Kamei (left) and a friend write ‘Ganbaro!’ (‘Hang in there!’) on a billboard in Ishinomaki.

Title: Tsunami
Description: Buddhist nun Jikou Yoshida prays amidst tsunami devastation, on 12 April.

Title: Tsunami
Description: A month after the tsunami, two-year-old Ayaka prays, together with other family members, for her grandmother and great-grandmother, at the spot where they used to live.

Title: Tsunami
Description: Hideo Kudo stands with his son Nagisa at the place where his missing father was last seen on 27 March.

Title: The New Amazons

Title: The Fight for Tahrir Square
Description: Peaceful demonstrations against the leadership of Egypt’s president Hosni Mubarak, on Tahrir Square in Cairo, turned violent in late January and early February, when Mubarak supporters attempted to storm the square and attack the protesters.

Title: The Fight for Tahrir Square
Description: A Mubarak supporter charges on a camel, on Tahrir Square, Cairo.

Title: The Fight for Tahrir Square
Description: Protesters hurl stones at Mubarak supporters to keep them out of Tahrir Square, on 3 February.

Title: The Fight for Tahrir Square
Description: Demonstrators retreat, as a group of Mubarak supporters advances on Tahrir Square.

Title: The Fight for Tahrir Square
Description: Protesters hold a captured Mubarak supporter, on Tahrir Square.

Title: The Fight for Tahrir Square
Description: Demonstrators on Tahrir Square react to a televised speech in which President Hosni Mubarak announced he would not be standing down, on 1 February.

Title: The Fight for Tahrir Square
Description: The body of a demonstrator, killed by a sniper, is removed from Tahrir Square, on 3 February.
